        "content": [
          {
            "type": "header",
            "text": "Key Points",
            "level": 2
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "items": [
              { "text": "Depression is a common cause of weight loss in the elderly." },
              { "text": "Hyperthyroidism in the elderly ('Apathetic Hyperthyroidism') may present solely with weight loss and atrial fibrillation, without the classic goitre or eye signs." },
              { "text": "Occult malignancy (e.g., Pancreatic, Renal, Lymphoma) can present with weight loss before localizing signs appear." },
              { "text": "If initial screening is negative, 'watchful waiting' with nutritional support is often appropriate unless symptoms evolve." }
            ]
          }
        ]
